<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xmlns:s="https://admin.wvusports.com/services/xml_schema/story" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"><channel><title>West Virginia University Athletics</title><link>https://admin.wvusports.com/rss.aspx</link><description>Latest news items for West Virginia University Athletics</description><atom:link href="https://admin.wvusports.com/rss" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml" /><language>en-us</language><ttl>60</ttl><item><title>Mountaineers Open Series Against TCU with Shutout</title><link>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/14/baseball-mountaineers-open-series-against-tcu-with-shutout</link><guid>https://wvusports.com/news/2026/5/14/baseball-mountaineers-open-series-against-tcu-with-shutout</guid><category>Baseball</category><description><![CDATA[<img alt="Ian Korn throws a pitch against TCU" src="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&image_path=/images/2026/5/14/051426_BSB_WVUvsTCU_CRC-6-2.jpg" /><br /><br />MORGANTOWN, W.Va. – The No. 9 West Virginia University baseball team opened its final series of the season with a 2-0 victory over TCU, Thursday night at Kendrick Family Ballpark. The Mountaineers improve to 36-12 and 20-8 in the Big 12, setting a program record for most conference wins. The Horned Frogs fall to 32-19 and 16-12 in conference play.]]></description><media:thumbnail url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_system&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/14/051426_BSB_WVUvsTCU_CRC-6-2.jpg" /><media:content url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/2026/5/14/051426_BSB_WVUvsTCU_CRC-6-2.jpg"><media:title>Ian Korn throws a pitch against TCU</media:title></media:content><enclosure url="https://admin.wvusports.com/common/controls/image_handler.aspx?thumb_prefix=rp_primary&amp;image_path=/images/202